    {
      "id": "69e5cf70_d0ac6c76",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2/components/dcae-bootstrap/resources/inputs/k8s-ves-inputs-tls.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "We don't want to move this configuration to property values file, because property value shouldn't be modificable by any one.\nIf we set external_port to 0 we are disabling port exposing outside the container.\n\nAdditionally I set external_port to 0, because I wanted to override default value of parameter from k8s-ves.yaml.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3435,
        "name": "Pawel Kasperkiewicz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pawel.kasperkiewicz@nokia.com",
        "username": "Pawel"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-25 10:33:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "7b9eb8e3_8e64631a",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "734c24b9_c490fc31",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2/components/dcae-bootstrap/resources/inputs/k8s-ves-inputs-tls.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "Yes - no need to expose external_port on tls input. My comment here was for external_port_tls (which is set on https://git.onap.org/oom/tree/kubernetes/dcaegen2/components/dcae-bootstrap/values.yaml). If someone wants to override the nodeport, they should be able to change it for TLS.",
      "author": {
